Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.82,0:01:04.28,Default,,0,0,0008,,{\blur3}宇宙:太阳的邪恶双子星--涅墨西斯
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.37,0:25:34.42,Default,,0,0,0008,,{\an8\blur3}为什么科学家们能观察到百万光年以外的天体
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.79,0:25:38.78,Default,,0,0,0008,,{\an8\blur3}却不能找出在我们太阳系边上的天体
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.62,0:26:00.74,Default,,0,0,0008,,{\an8\blur3}询问宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.29,0:00:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上溯至宇宙初始 周遭还只是一片漆黑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the beginning, there was darkness.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.62,0:00:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不知何时 忽地一声巨响{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And then... Bang!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.69,0:00:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时间空间以及物质皆由此发端{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Giving birth to an endless expanding existence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.49,0:00:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}此后不断膨胀 延伸 永无止境{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of time, space, and matter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.02,0:00:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一天 新的发现都在不断为我们解开{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Every day, new discoveries are unlocking{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.48,0:00:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}蕴藏于这里的那些神秘莫测{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the mysterious, the mind-blowing,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.60,0:00:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}令人大开眼界 致命的秘密{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the deadly secrets of a place we call{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.61,0:00:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们称这个地方为"宇宙"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the universe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.37,0:00:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的太阳是否有一颗邪恶伴星呢{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Could our Sun have an evil companion?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.23,0:00:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是否有这样一颗未被发现的死星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}An undiscovered death star{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.39,0:00:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在最遥远的太阳系边界处旋转 徘徊{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}rotating at the furthest edges of the Solar System?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.96,0:00:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这颗神秘的恒星是否每隔一段时间{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Does this mysterious star scatter destruction{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.94,0:00:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就为太阳系埋带来毁灭性的灾难{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}through the Solar System at regular intervals,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.89,0:00:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它是否造成了地球史上最大规模的灭绝呢{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}accounting for the greatest extinctions in Earth's history?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.80,0:00:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学家敏锐的目光穿过这个充斥着巨恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Sifting through a realm populated by giant worlds{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.73,0:00:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以及神秘的小恒星的地带 去搜寻{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and mysterious planetoids, scientists are on the hunt{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.57,0:00:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳的邪恶双子星--涅墨西斯{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}for Nemesis--The Sun's evil twin.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们头顶上闪烁的数以亿万计的群星之中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Of the billions of stars twinkling overhead,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.48,0:01:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有一颗也许会使地球上生灵涂炭{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}one may be a scourge to life on Earth...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.03,0:01:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就是太阳的邪恶双子星--涅墨西斯{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}An evil twin to the Sun named Nemesis.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.04,0:01:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有些科学家怀疑 涅墨西斯是一颗{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Some scientists suspect that Nemesis is{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.56,0:01:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不发光且尚未发现的围绕太阳转动的恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}a dark, still-undiscovered star orbiting our Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.49,0:01:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而每过两千六百万年{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And every 26 million years,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.52,0:01:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就会带来一场灾难{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it triggers a disaster.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.51,0:01:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大家都知道 太阳系的周围{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We know that the Solar System{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.05,0:01:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}环绕着巨大的彗星团{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is surrounded by this enormous cloud of comets,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.44,0:01:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此太阳伴星这一系列运动产生的轨迹{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and so these successive passages of the Sun's companion{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.36,0:01:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将会把一些彗星带入太阳系的内部{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}would send comets into the inner Solar System.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.56,0:01:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们有可能撞击地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Some of them will hit Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.33,0:01:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而一旦撞击发生 地球将生灵涂炭{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}What follows is death on a colossal scale.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.00,0:02:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在普遍的理论是 在六千五百万年前{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It is now widely accepted that a rock from space{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.47,0:02:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一块来自太空的岩石结束了恐龙时代{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}caused the end of the age of dinosaurs 65 million years ago.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.74,0:02:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们现在已有十足的把握认定{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So we now are pretty convinced that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.36,0:02:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}六千五百万年前的那场{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the reason that a huge fraction of life on the Earth{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.02,0:02:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}令地球大部分物种灭绝的灾难{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}went extinct 65 million years ago{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.06,0:02:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是由于一颗彗星撞击地球而造成的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}was because a comet slammed into the Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.97,0:02:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但天文学家理查德·穆勒却提出了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But astronomer Richard Muller has proposed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.61,0:02:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一套革命性的理论 以解释为何彗星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}a revolutionary theory to explain why that space rock{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.55,0:02:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}会恰巧在那一时刻撞击地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}crashed to Earth at that particular moment.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.92,0:02:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}涅墨西斯理论描述了这一假想{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Nemesis theory postulates that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.57,0:02:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}即 有一颗恒星在做绕日运动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there's a star orbiting the Sun{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.27,0:02:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而其公转周期为两千六百万年{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}at a 26-million-year period.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.12,0:02:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}足矣{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That's about it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.77,0:02:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几乎不需要其它假说来支持此理论了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Almost no other assumptions need to be made.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.43,0:03:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}穆勒认为当涅墨西斯运行到太阳附近时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Muller believes that as Nemesis nears the Sun,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.38,0:03:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它所带来的引力扰乱{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}its gravitational disturbance{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.33,0:03:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}会使得一些彗星穿越太阳系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}sends comets flying through the Solar System.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.44,0:03:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种现象的后果就是造成地球历史上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The resulting impacts have been the source of{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.78,0:03:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}多次大规模物种灭绝现象的元凶{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}many major extinction events in Earth's history.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.92,0:03:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}穆勒这样解释他的理论是如何诞生的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Muller explains how the theory came about.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.68,0:03:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有两位古生物学者{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Two paleontologists,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.21,0:03:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在研究地球生物灭绝的规律时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}when looking at patterns of extinctions,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.12,0:03:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发现了一件似乎十分不可思议的事情{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}came across something that seemed utterly insane.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.41,0:03:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们说 这种类似的灭绝现象{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They said that similar extinctions were taking place{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.56,0:03:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大约每两千六百万年就要发生一次{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}every 26 million years on a regular schedule.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.58,0:03:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}任何地球本身的现象都似乎都无法解释{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The discovery of a 26-million-year pattern of extinctions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.79,0:03:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个每两千六百万年的物种灭绝规律{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}seemed impossible to explain by any process native to the Earth itself.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.45,0:03:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这可是科学家们梦寐以求的事情{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}This is the sort of thing you dream about in science.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.74,0:03:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为这说明有些事物对我们还是未知{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It means there's something we don't understand.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.32,0:03:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}说明有未知的事物亟待发现{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It means there's a discovery waiting.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.01,0:03:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}于是 我便试图去探求那未解之谜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So I set about trying to figure out what that was.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.51,0:04:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}穆勒提出了一个惊人的假说{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Muller made an astonishing proposal.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.77,0:04:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些周期性灭绝现象的唯一合理解释就是{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The only logical cause of these periodic extinctions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.00,0:04:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有一颗潜恒星 它每两千六百万年饶太阳一周{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is a cosmic stalker that orbits our Sun every 26 million years,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.92,0:04:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而每一接近太阳就会造成彗星轨道的紊乱{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}disturbing the comets on each approach.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.57,0:04:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}总之 它是一颗太阳的死亡伴星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In short, a death star companion to our Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.84,0:04:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果真的发现这颗恒星 将是意义深远的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If this star is discovered, it is so important.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它在地球上生物进化过程中起到了重要作用{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It was a major player in the evolution of life on Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.34,0:04:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}若不是这颗恒星 也许恐龙还在称霸地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Without this, perhaps the dinosaurs would still be here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.38,0:04:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果穆勒所言属实{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If Muller is right,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.63,0:04:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那么人类之所以能够出现在地球上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}humanity itself could owe its existence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.83,0:04:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还是多亏了这颗名叫涅墨西斯的死星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to the Nemesis death star.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.15,0:04:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}毕竟每次大规模灭绝都清除了大量物种{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}After all, each mass extinction wiped out vast numbers of species,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.06,0:04:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但这也为新物种的出现和繁衍开辟了道路{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but each also cleared the way for new species to arise,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.47,0:04:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其中就包括 最后出现的人类{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}including, ultimately, humans.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.85,0:05:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通过在加州的圣塔罗莎高原的可控火灾{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We can witness the way Nemesis would have altered evolution on Earth{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.04,0:05:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们便知道涅墨西斯是如何影响地球生物进化的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}by looking at a controlled burn on the Santa rosa plateau in California.{\r}
